The Nigerian Customs Service (NCS), Federal Operation Unit (FOU), Zone ‘B’, has made seizures of 379 packs of 225mg tramadol along Kano/Kazaure road. Other items apprehended include 150 cartons of veterinary drugs without NAFDAC Registration arrested along Jibiya axis, 816 bags of NPK 15:15:15 fertilizer also along jibiya axis, 100 kegs of vegetable oil, and 2 trucks loaded with tiger nuts and dates. Also seized were 676 bags of 50kg parboiled foreign rice and 60 bales of second hand clothing. According to the Comptroller FOU of Zone B, Mustapha Sarkin-Kebbi, while briefing newsmen, said all the seizures which were made within two weeks amidst the lockdown is worth N56,577,500 Duty Paid Value (DPV). He said the smugglers have devised various means of concealing their smuggled items, stressing, however, that his personnel are equally up to the task in busting their tactics. The seized parboiled foreign rice, which was intercepted along Kaduna-Zaria road, were concealed inside fire wood and in sacks that looked like that of charcoals, some were bagged in Nigeria labeled sacks. The Comptroller disclosed that the driver conveying the seized tramadol escaped into the bush upon sensing trouble. 